1
00:00:06,027 --> 00:00:08,779
-[birds twittering]
-[dog barking in distance]

2
00:00:23,044 --> 00:00:24,336
[sighs]

3
00:00:41,729 --> 00:00:42,813
[exhales]

4
00:01:00,664 --> 00:01:01,874
[Woo-jin sighs]

5
00:01:03,709 --> 00:01:04,627
[tuts]

6
00:01:04,710 --> 00:01:05,795
ACK

7
00:01:05,878 --> 00:01:07,171
[Woo-jin] Don't worry.

8
00:01:10,549 --> 00:01:13,469
You can count on me.

9
00:01:16,055 --> 00:01:16,889
Woo-jin.

10
00:01:19,558 --> 00:01:20,726
What?

11
00:01:22,645 --> 00:01:23,813
Your mouth stinks of poo.

12
00:01:23,896 --> 00:01:24,814
Hey, Gun-woo.

13
00:01:24,897 --> 00:01:28,234
That's not something
you say in the morning to anyone.

14
00:01:28,317 --> 00:01:29,735
Smell it. It's poo breath.

15
00:01:30,528 --> 00:01:34,198
Are you sick or you caught a cold?
We'll go to the hospital after training.

16
00:01:38,035 --> 00:01:39,328
[sniffs]

17
00:01:39,411 --> 00:01:40,371
[exhales]

18
00:01:40,913 --> 00:01:43,165
[coughs, sniffs]

19
00:01:43,999 --> 00:01:46,001
[upbeat music playing]

20
00:01:53,384 --> 00:01:55,052
[footsteps thudding]

21
00:01:55,136 --> 00:01:56,512
[groans]

22
00:01:58,514 --> 00:02:00,516
Oh jeez, those boys.

23
00:02:04,812 --> 00:02:07,064
[both sigh]

24
00:02:07,148 --> 00:02:08,941
-Ready! Ack!
-Ack!

25
00:02:09,024 --> 00:02:09,942
Go!

26
00:02:10,025 --> 00:02:12,528
-[rock music playing]
-[both panting]

27
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,364
-Let's eat the competition!
-Ack!

28
00:02:27,376 --> 00:02:31,714
[both exhaling sharply]

29
00:02:41,849 --> 00:02:43,392
-[Gun-woo grunts]
-Number three!

30
00:02:46,061 --> 00:02:47,062
Ack!

31
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:48,022
[grunts]

32
00:02:48,647 --> 00:02:49,690
[breathing deeply]

33
00:02:51,483 --> 00:02:52,484
[music fades]

34
00:02:55,279 --> 00:02:57,281
[tranquil music playing]

35
00:02:58,407 --> 00:03:00,367
-Please enjoy these.
-Yes, ma'am, thanks.

36
00:03:01,535 --> 00:03:02,745
-[So-yeon] Gun-woo.
-Hi, Mom.

37
00:03:02,828 --> 00:03:05,289
I've got a delivery!
Woo-jin, make me two espressos?

38
00:03:05,372 --> 00:03:06,832
-Drive safely.
-[Gun-woo] I will.

39
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:08,626
Here, let's do this.

40
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:10,753
-[Gun-woo] See you soon.
-[So-yeon] Okay.

41
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:40,616
MOVING ON FRIDAY, 2/14
THANK YOU FOR YOUR UNDERSTANDING

42
00:03:42,618 --> 00:03:44,328
BUILDING 104
UNIT 1901

43
00:03:53,587 --> 00:03:56,257
Jeong-gwon, how about
putting that over inside there?

44
00:03:57,508 --> 00:03:59,426
-Yes, I ordered those.
-Here you are.

45
00:04:00,302 --> 00:04:01,720
Whoa!

46
00:04:02,596 --> 00:04:04,098
You're the boxer, Kim Gun-woo, right?

47
00:04:04,181 --> 00:04:05,641
-Yes, hi.
-Could I maybe…

48
00:04:05,724 --> 00:04:06,892
Shake? Sure.

49
00:04:07,810 --> 00:04:09,436
You've got a strong hand.

50
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,562
[exhales]

51
00:04:11,188 --> 00:04:14,942
Ah, sorry about making you use the stairs.
There's a lot of them.

52
00:04:15,025 --> 00:04:17,653
No, that's okay.
I enjoy taking the stairs.

53
00:04:17,736 --> 00:04:21,323
It's good. I end up working muscles
I don't normally use when I'm boxing

54
00:04:21,407 --> 00:04:22,908
so it helps improve my balance.

55
00:04:23,492 --> 00:04:24,493
[gasps] Oh.

56
00:04:26,203 --> 00:04:27,413
You're really amazing.

57
00:04:28,122 --> 00:04:29,873
I'm an athlete too. In tae kwon do.

58
00:04:30,541 --> 00:04:31,834
Oh, whoa, wow.

59
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:34,003
[music fades]

60
00:04:39,508 --> 00:04:40,759
You fight too?

61
00:04:42,177 --> 00:04:43,012
Uh, that's…

62
00:04:47,391 --> 00:04:49,727
I'm not a talker.
I'm so sorry for being shy.

63
00:04:50,894 --> 00:04:53,022
I'll root for you
in the championship match. Go win!

64
00:04:53,105 --> 00:04:54,481
[chuckles] Yes, win!

65
00:04:54,982 --> 00:04:56,108
Please enjoy!

66
00:04:56,608 --> 00:04:58,068
-I will.
-Good.

67
00:05:00,821 --> 00:05:02,448
Wow, this hand touched his.

68
00:05:03,324 --> 00:05:04,491
Jeong-gwon, look!

69
00:05:04,575 --> 00:05:05,576
[Woo-jin exhales]

70
00:05:06,243 --> 00:05:07,244
Here.

71
00:05:08,162 --> 00:05:08,996
Let's sit.

72
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:11,081
[tranquil music playing]

73
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:13,500
Thanks for the meal.

74
00:05:13,584 --> 00:05:14,877
-Okay.
-Thanks for the meal.

75
00:05:19,423 --> 00:05:21,717
Gun-woo, don't you
still have to lose some weight?

76
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,594
Hmm.

77
00:05:26,388 --> 00:05:27,848
You think he's going to be okay?

78
00:05:27,931 --> 00:05:30,601
Don't worry about his weight.
It'll quickly fall off him.

79
00:05:31,101 --> 00:05:33,771
-Gun-woo, you'll make the weigh-in?
-Mm.

80
00:05:34,355 --> 00:05:35,189
Hmm.

81
00:05:38,984 --> 00:05:40,778
Gun-woo, keep listening to him.

82
00:05:41,403 --> 00:05:42,279
Mm.

83
00:05:42,363 --> 00:05:44,323
And you, look after him, Woo-jin.

84
00:05:44,907 --> 00:05:45,824
Mm.

85
00:05:45,908 --> 00:05:48,160
-Mm. [chuckles]
-[music fades]

86
00:05:48,243 --> 00:05:49,119
[all chuckle]

87
00:05:49,203 --> 00:05:51,205
-[So-yeon] Mm, mm.
-[all chuckle]

88
00:05:51,288 --> 00:05:52,998
[announcer] Bring the fighters
to the scale

89
00:05:53,082 --> 00:05:56,335
for the WBC World Super-Middleweight
title match.

90
00:05:56,418 --> 00:05:57,252
[man] Yeah!

91
00:05:57,336 --> 00:06:00,881
[announcer] First for the weigh-in,
we have champion, Adik Belov!

92
00:06:01,465 --> 00:06:03,967
Belov has stepped onto the scale
and he's made weight!

93
00:06:04,051 --> 00:06:07,930
Yeah! [grunting]

94
00:06:08,013 --> 00:06:10,641
[announcer] Next we have for the weigh-in,
his opponent, Kim Gun-woo.

95
00:06:10,724 --> 00:06:11,683
[Woo-jin cheers]

96
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:13,185
[tense music playing]

97
00:06:16,939 --> 00:06:18,982
Kim stands on the scale
and he's made weight.

98
00:06:19,066 --> 00:06:21,735
[cheering, whooping]

99
00:06:23,737 --> 00:06:27,408
In 26 hours, we'll have champion
Adik Belov against Kim Gun-woo

100
00:06:27,491 --> 00:06:28,742
in an exciting match.

101
00:06:28,826 --> 00:06:32,162
Fighters, come to the center of the stage
to face your opponent.

102
00:06:35,207 --> 00:06:38,001
I'm gonna bust your face open!

103
00:06:38,085 --> 00:06:39,920
I kill you!

104
00:06:40,421 --> 00:06:42,297
You are dead tomorrow.

105
00:06:49,221 --> 00:06:51,432
-Hey, are you crazy?!
-[man 3] Break it up!

106
00:06:51,515 --> 00:06:52,808
[man 4] They're fighting.

107
00:06:52,891 --> 00:06:55,477
[man 1] We'd like to remind the staff
to calm the fighters down.

108
00:06:55,561 --> 00:06:57,980
There's no need
for any of this to start now.

109
00:06:58,063 --> 00:07:02,901
[clamoring]

110
00:07:17,207 --> 00:07:19,209
[ominous music playing]

111
00:07:29,261 --> 00:07:30,929
[exhales]

112
00:07:53,035 --> 00:07:55,037
[suspenseful rock music playing]

113
00:08:20,187 --> 00:08:21,063
[music fades]

114
00:08:21,146 --> 00:08:23,398
BLOODHOUNDS 2

115
00:08:24,525 --> 00:08:27,110
We're moments away! I'm Hong Seok-hyeon.

116
00:08:27,194 --> 00:08:31,031
And Kim Kwang-sun, the gold medalist
of the '88 Olympics, is here with me!

117
00:08:31,114 --> 00:08:32,407
Thank you very much. Hello.

118
00:08:32,491 --> 00:08:36,161
Tonight, we'll be watching the WBC
world super middleweight title match

119
00:08:36,245 --> 00:08:37,871
between Adik Belov and Kim Gun-woo.

120
00:08:37,955 --> 00:08:40,332
First, Kim Gun-woo
has made a remarkable rise

121
00:08:40,415 --> 00:08:44,253
since he won the KBFC Rookie
of the Year Tournament five years ago.

122
00:08:44,336 --> 00:08:47,130
Tonight, he's up for the championship
title. Do you think he'll win?

123
00:08:47,214 --> 00:08:48,799
He's risen quickly in the boxing world.

124
00:08:48,882 --> 00:08:51,093
I'm proud of him,
and I think he can do it.

125
00:08:51,176 --> 00:08:53,554
[Seok-hyeon] The fighters have entered.
We're about to begin.

126
00:08:53,637 --> 00:08:58,100
Adik Belov has refused to touch gloves.
This is a power move on Belov's part.

127
00:08:58,183 --> 00:09:01,728
[Kwang-sun] This shows that Belov
is engaging in a psychological war.

128
00:09:01,812 --> 00:09:04,481
[Seok-hyeon] Who knows if that'll pay off?
Fans seem split.

129
00:09:04,565 --> 00:09:09,027
Round one begins, and Adik Belov
again pushes away Kim Gun-woo's glove.

130
00:09:09,111 --> 00:09:11,071
Kim jabs and Belov goes in for the attack.

131
00:09:11,154 --> 00:09:12,823
[Kwang-sun] He's coming on strong.

132
00:09:12,906 --> 00:09:16,618
[Seok-hyeon] Kim punches back, but Belov
aggressively puts Kim into a corner.

133
00:09:16,702 --> 00:09:20,956
Belov's taking control early,
using combinations with speed and power.

134
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:23,667
-[Kwang-sun] Kim needs to start fighting.
-[Seok-hyeon] That's true.

135
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:27,045
Belov and Kim square off
as Kim steps forward and starts punching.

136
00:09:27,129 --> 00:09:28,880
A combination of jabs and a right hook.

137
00:09:28,964 --> 00:09:30,674
-Oh!
-[Kwang-sun] Oh!

138
00:09:30,757 --> 00:09:31,842
[high-pitched ringing]

139
00:09:31,925 --> 00:09:33,093
[referee, muffled] Two!

140
00:09:34,094 --> 00:09:35,304
Three!

141
00:09:36,555 --> 00:09:37,806
Four!

142
00:09:38,473 --> 00:09:41,018
[Seok-hyeon] Belov's counter stunned Kim,
knocking him down.

143
00:09:41,101 --> 00:09:44,062
It was as if Kim
was walking right into Belov's plan.

144
00:09:44,146 --> 00:09:45,147
[inaudible speech]

145
00:09:45,731 --> 00:09:46,773
[referee] Six.

146
00:09:46,857 --> 00:09:49,401
[tense music continues]

147
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:54,072
What happens if Adik wins?

148
00:09:54,156 --> 00:09:56,950
He'll pay you. The prize money
will be used to pay off his debt.

149
00:09:57,034 --> 00:09:59,911
Then why the fuck did I come
if I didn't have to be here?

150
00:09:59,995 --> 00:10:01,413
I'll drag him in no matter what.

151
00:10:02,247 --> 00:10:04,416
Get that bastard in the fucking cage.

152
00:10:05,709 --> 00:10:06,793
Got it.

153
00:10:09,671 --> 00:10:11,882
Win this! You can do it!

154
00:10:14,885 --> 00:10:16,094
It's okay, it's fine.

155
00:10:18,263 --> 00:10:19,931
-Box!
-[Gun-woo exhales]

156
00:10:20,015 --> 00:10:23,185
[Seok-hyeon] Kim Gun-woo's going to be
cautious of Adik Belov's left hook now

157
00:10:23,268 --> 00:10:24,895
because he got caught badly by it.

158
00:10:24,978 --> 00:10:27,939
[Kwang-sun] Kim's an all-around fighter
and he needs to start stepping it up.

159
00:10:28,023 --> 00:10:30,442
-[Seok-hyeon] What a duck!
-[Kwang-sun] Belov being aggressive.

160
00:10:30,525 --> 00:10:32,903
Kim backs away.
He needs to show some combos.

161
00:10:32,986 --> 00:10:36,198
[Seok-hyeon] Can Kim Gun-woo stop
Adik Belov's momentum and find his own?

162
00:10:36,281 --> 00:10:38,283
[Kwang-sun] He got hit in the face again
as he ducks.

163
00:10:38,367 --> 00:10:40,577
[Seok-hyeon] Belov backed Kim Gun-woo
into a corner again.

164
00:10:40,661 --> 00:10:43,121
[Kwang-sun] Belov keeps showing
his finesse in this first round.

165
00:10:43,205 --> 00:10:46,166
The clinch tactic Kim just did
broke it up and was good.

166
00:10:46,249 --> 00:10:49,002
[Seok-hyeon] Kim Gun-woo's
trying to stop Belov's momentum.

167
00:10:49,503 --> 00:10:51,380
[Kwang-sun] Kim's normally
an aggressive fighter,

168
00:10:51,463 --> 00:10:53,048
but he keeps getting pushed back.

169
00:10:53,131 --> 00:10:55,550
[Seok-hyeon] Gun-woo steps back again.
This isn't going well.

170
00:10:55,634 --> 00:10:58,428
[Kwang-sun] It's clear
Kim's taken some damage already.

171
00:10:58,512 --> 00:11:01,890
[Seok-hyeon] Belov hooks left and right,
driving Kim into the corner again.

172
00:11:01,973 --> 00:11:04,476
[Kwang-sun] And Kim backs up
and babysits the corner.

173
00:11:04,976 --> 00:11:08,188
[Seok-hyeon] Right jab, left jab.
Adik keeps attacking!

174
00:11:08,689 --> 00:11:10,273
[Kwang-sun] Kim clinches Adik again.

175
00:11:10,357 --> 00:11:13,568
[Seok-hyeon] Kim's tactic seems to be
to hold off Adik for as long as possible.

176
00:11:13,652 --> 00:11:16,947
[Kwang-sun] First round's over
and Adik Belov clearly dominated.

177
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:19,741
[Seok-hyeon] Yes.
And that's the end of the first round.

178
00:11:22,536 --> 00:11:24,788
His punches are quick.
His infighting's good.

179
00:11:24,871 --> 00:11:26,998
-[Woo-jin] Catch your breath.
-[Gun-woo panting]

180
00:11:27,082 --> 00:11:28,750
-[Woo-jin] Focus.
-[panting]

181
00:11:28,834 --> 00:11:32,379
[Woo-jin] Don't let him get to you.
Be in his face and don't back down.

182
00:11:32,462 --> 00:11:34,381
You know there's no one alive
who can beat you.

183
00:11:35,549 --> 00:11:36,425
[exhales]

184
00:11:37,008 --> 00:11:37,926
Look at me, man.

185
00:11:38,009 --> 00:11:41,346
[breathes deeply]

186
00:11:43,348 --> 00:11:44,182
Kim Gun-woo.

187
00:11:47,644 --> 00:11:50,355
Trust your infighting.
Trust what we've built.

188
00:11:53,191 --> 00:11:54,651
Eat the competition.

189
00:11:54,735 --> 00:11:56,737
[suspenseful music playing]

190
00:11:59,656 --> 00:12:02,325
Number three's loading.
Calling in the order.

191
00:12:03,076 --> 00:12:04,286
-Ack!
-[yells] Ack!

192
00:12:04,369 --> 00:12:05,412
[grunts] Ack!

193
00:12:11,918 --> 00:12:13,670
-[bell dings]
-[grunts]

194
00:12:13,754 --> 00:12:15,338
[Seok-hyeon] Round two begins.

195
00:12:15,839 --> 00:12:18,300
Kim looks more determined
at the start of this second round.

196
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,137
[Kwang-sun] Kim's being more aggressive.
It's good to see him not back away.

197
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:25,974
[Seok-hyeon] It's great. Kim gives
well-landed body blows to Belov's side,

198
00:12:26,057 --> 00:12:27,392
followed with quick combos.

199
00:12:27,476 --> 00:12:29,644
[Kwang-sun] It's a great series
of uppercuts and a hook.

200
00:12:29,728 --> 00:12:31,438
[Seok-hyeon] Now, it's Belov retreating.

201
00:12:31,521 --> 00:12:34,316
[Kwang-sun] Kim's fighting
more like his usual style now.

202
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:37,402
[Seok-hyeon] Kim's displaying
his infighting technique and combos

203
00:12:37,486 --> 00:12:38,361
in this second round.

204
00:12:38,445 --> 00:12:41,948
[Kwang-sun] His coach must've reminded him
who he is and what he's here to do.

205
00:12:42,032 --> 00:12:44,659
He needed to be more aggressive
than he was in the first round.

206
00:12:44,743 --> 00:12:47,454
[Seok-hyeon] Kim mixes up his striking
combos as he closes the distance

207
00:12:47,537 --> 00:12:49,039
with a series to Belov's head and body.

208
00:12:49,122 --> 00:12:51,833
[Kwang-sun] Those punches land quickly
with force and precision.

209
00:12:51,917 --> 00:12:54,753
-[Seok-hyeon] Belov into the corner.
-[Kwang-sun] Things have turned!

210
00:12:54,836 --> 00:12:56,963
-Number three!
-[Seok-hyeon] Kim's got the upper hand.

211
00:12:57,047 --> 00:13:00,926
He delivers a barrage of blows to Belov.
Kim keeps pouring on the punches!

212
00:13:01,009 --> 00:13:03,303
[Kwang-sun] Those were
fast and tight combos.

213
00:13:04,513 --> 00:13:07,307
[Seok-hyeon] Kim lands
a perfect straight punch!

214
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:09,184
[Kwang-sun] It had power, speed and force.

215
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:11,019
-[bell rings]
-[Seok-hyeon] What?

216
00:13:11,102 --> 00:13:15,065
I can't believe this. He stopped.
That would've been the finishing blow.

217
00:13:15,148 --> 00:13:16,817
[Kwang-sun] He would've won.
But he stopped.

218
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:20,195
That punch was going straight to the eye
and would've landed cleanly.

219
00:13:20,278 --> 00:13:21,571
But Kim stopped.

220
00:13:21,655 --> 00:13:24,032
-He stopped it just as the bell rang.
-Yeah.

221
00:13:24,115 --> 00:13:27,369
The sportsmanship tonight.
It shows what kind of athlete Kim is.

222
00:13:27,452 --> 00:13:31,748
[Seok-hyeon] In the second round,
Kim not only showed his commanding skills,

223
00:13:31,832 --> 00:13:33,834
but also his sportsmanship to his fans.

224
00:13:33,917 --> 00:13:36,253
Kim had a great momentum
in the second round.

225
00:13:36,336 --> 00:13:37,921
His fans are on fire.

226
00:13:38,004 --> 00:13:40,924
I'm looking forward to what
we'll see from him in the third round.

227
00:13:41,007 --> 00:13:43,009
[crowd] Kim Gun-woo! Kim Gun-woo!

228
00:13:43,093 --> 00:13:44,261
-This one's yours.
-Yeah?

229
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:46,972
Belov's got a gash on his left eye.

230
00:13:47,055 --> 00:13:49,349
Finish him off
with your right jab quickly.

231
00:13:50,934 --> 00:13:52,727
[Belov] Stop the blood! How's it looking?

232
00:13:52,811 --> 00:13:53,895
-[Gun-woo] Woo-jin.
-Yeah?

233
00:13:54,938 --> 00:13:56,398
Can't we go with number one?

234
00:13:56,481 --> 00:13:58,400
We're almost finished. Why change?

235
00:13:58,483 --> 00:14:00,360
-I gotta fight!
-[coach] I need you to focus.

236
00:14:00,443 --> 00:14:01,987
-I need to win!
-[coach] Focus!

237
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:03,864
He'll need a dozen stitches to his face.

238
00:14:04,364 --> 00:14:06,157
I can still win
by using number one instead.

239
00:14:06,241 --> 00:14:07,701
No way. Too risky.

240
00:14:07,784 --> 00:14:08,702
He's the champion.

241
00:14:08,785 --> 00:14:11,621
You've got to stay the course and finish
it off when you have the chance.

242
00:14:11,705 --> 00:14:12,873
[suspenseful music playing]

243
00:14:12,956 --> 00:14:17,002
We should trust the number one.
Trust what we've made and who we are.

244
00:14:18,837 --> 00:14:20,088
[coach] It's just you and me.

245
00:14:20,171 --> 00:14:23,466
He's gonna attack that left eye
with a right hook or a right straight.

246
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,969
Duck it, get in close,
and finish this thing.

247
00:14:26,052 --> 00:14:27,429
-Yeah.
-[coach] Do that for me?

248
00:14:28,513 --> 00:14:29,347
I understand.

249
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:31,141
[chuckles softly]

250
00:14:31,224 --> 00:14:34,352
So instead, punch him very quickly.

251
00:14:34,436 --> 00:14:36,187
Mm-hmm. Fast.

252
00:14:36,897 --> 00:14:38,481
Like the speed of light!

253
00:14:38,565 --> 00:14:39,858
Lightening!

254
00:14:40,483 --> 00:14:41,860
-[grunts] Ack!
-[grunts] Ack!

255
00:14:42,777 --> 00:14:44,195
-Ack!
-[grunts]

256
00:14:44,279 --> 00:14:45,322
-Go!
-[grunts]

257
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:47,908
[grunts]

258
00:14:47,991 --> 00:14:49,993
[dramatic music playing]

259
00:14:54,748 --> 00:14:56,416
You'll win this for Uzbekistan, Adik!

260
00:15:03,006 --> 00:15:04,925
[Seok-hyeon] Round three begins.

261
00:15:05,592 --> 00:15:09,721
Kim raises his guard, and he rushes
forward as Adik stays frozen.

262
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:14,309
Kim lands a left hook onto Adik's side!

263
00:15:14,935 --> 00:15:17,687
[Kwang-sun] It went clean
on the right side of Adik's body.

264
00:15:17,771 --> 00:15:21,399
[Seok-hyeon] Wow, Belov quickly collapses.
Will he be able to get up?

265
00:15:21,483 --> 00:15:24,486
-You can do it! Come on!
-[Kwang-sun] Didn't take that punch well.

266
00:15:24,569 --> 00:15:27,155
[Seok-hyeon] Belov's still
down on the ground, in pain.

267
00:15:27,238 --> 00:15:30,408
Belov took some heavy damage!
Is this the end?

268
00:15:30,992 --> 00:15:32,827
-Nine.
-[Seok-hyeon] We're at the count of nine.

269
00:15:32,911 --> 00:15:35,497
-The match has been called!
-[cheering]

270
00:15:35,580 --> 00:15:36,748
It's over!

271
00:15:36,831 --> 00:15:38,917
[Kwang-sun] Kim gave a fight-ending KO.

272
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,629
[Seok-hyeon] Kim Gun-woo is the new
WBC super middleweight champion!

273
00:15:43,213 --> 00:15:49,886
[crowd] Kim Gun-woo! Kim Gun-woo!
Kim Gun-woo! Kim Gun-woo!

274
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,680
[Gun-woo] Are you okay?

275
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:57,686
[crowd] Kim Gun-woo! Kim Gun-woo!
Kim Gun-woo! Kim Gun-woo!

276
00:15:57,769 --> 00:16:00,730
You're a good fighter. Forget what I said.

277
00:16:00,814 --> 00:16:02,273
It's just business.

278
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:04,734
Thank you.

279
00:16:10,156 --> 00:16:12,993
[rock music playing]

280
00:16:13,827 --> 00:16:15,370
[Woo-jin yells]

281
00:16:15,453 --> 00:16:18,748
[both yell]

282
00:16:18,832 --> 00:16:20,792
[screams happily]

283
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:25,714
[all yell happily]

284
00:16:25,797 --> 00:16:28,466
-[music fades]
-[Woo-jin] Gun-woo, see what I got. Look.

285
00:16:30,927 --> 00:16:33,221
[Woo-jin coughing]

286
00:16:35,015 --> 00:16:36,933
Gross. Why do people smoke this?

287
00:16:37,017 --> 00:16:37,892
Throw it out.

288
00:16:37,976 --> 00:16:41,229
-No way. This… [coughs] …cost 100,000 won.
-It did?

289
00:16:41,312 --> 00:16:42,230
But I'll throw it.

290
00:16:42,313 --> 00:16:43,732
I'll throw it away.

291
00:16:43,815 --> 00:16:45,567
Done. It was nice.

292
00:16:46,276 --> 00:16:47,152
Having the cigar.

293
00:16:47,736 --> 00:16:49,154
You just wasted money though.

294
00:16:49,237 --> 00:16:52,532
[exhales] Hey, we used to be so broke

295
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:55,577
we could barely afford the buffets.

296
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:57,620
Now, we throw cigars away.

297
00:16:58,204 --> 00:17:00,749
And now you're the champion. The winner!

298
00:17:00,832 --> 00:17:01,833
[both laugh]

299
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:02,959
For real. [chuckles]

300
00:17:03,043 --> 00:17:04,544
[chuckles]

301
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,966
It feels like yesterday
we took down Kim Myeong-gil.

302
00:17:11,009 --> 00:17:12,761
It's gone by so quickly.

303
00:17:15,722 --> 00:17:17,015
[exhales]

304
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:19,434
What now?

305
00:17:20,935 --> 00:17:21,853
Woo-jin,

306
00:17:22,771 --> 00:17:25,732
should we go visit Mr. Choi's grave
with the championship belt?

307
00:17:25,815 --> 00:17:27,817
[poignant music playing]

308
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:30,445
Geez, you've grown up.
Not like your coach.

309
00:17:31,321 --> 00:17:33,031
-I know.
-What?

310
00:17:33,615 --> 00:17:34,699
I'm just playing!

311
00:17:34,783 --> 00:17:35,909
[both laugh]

312
00:17:35,992 --> 00:17:38,578
You've grown so much now
you even know how to joke around.

313
00:17:38,661 --> 00:17:41,539
-I learned that from you.
-[both chuckle]

314
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,376
Do you know why I'm grateful to you?

315
00:17:45,877 --> 00:17:48,129
-Huh?
-Im, the loan shark.

316
00:17:48,213 --> 00:17:51,841
When we went to borrow money
from that guy, he said he'd lend it

317
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:54,677
if we became bloodhounds.

318
00:17:54,761 --> 00:17:56,137
That was his stipulation.

319
00:17:56,805 --> 00:17:59,057
[Im] Here's a first-tier loan
of 100 million.

320
00:17:59,557 --> 00:18:01,935
In exchange, you'll do some work for me.

321
00:18:04,646 --> 00:18:07,732
I would probably
be beating people up for money…

322
00:18:10,443 --> 00:18:13,279
if you hadn't told me to leave
when he asked us.

323
00:18:14,656 --> 00:18:15,824
It's thanks to you, Gun-woo,

324
00:18:17,408 --> 00:18:19,202
that this belt's here, with us.

325
00:18:19,953 --> 00:18:20,995
[Gun-woo] No, not at all.

326
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:23,665
You're the reason.

327
00:18:24,249 --> 00:18:25,750
You're why we're here now.

328
00:18:27,460 --> 00:18:31,005
Without you, we wouldn't have been able
to take down Kim Myeong-gil.

329
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:32,966
And also,

330
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:37,220
I wouldn't have been able to make it
this far. Not if I stayed with Coach Kim.

331
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:42,058
It's all because of you that we're here,

332
00:18:42,559 --> 00:18:44,477
and as champions of the world.

333
00:18:45,478 --> 00:18:48,231
Retiring as a boxer
and working as your coach

334
00:18:50,150 --> 00:18:51,860
was the only decision

335
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:54,487
I could have done to change our lives.

336
00:18:55,905 --> 00:18:58,575
But we're not stopping here.
We're going onwards.

337
00:18:59,075 --> 00:19:01,327
Let's be the champions of the universe.

338
00:19:01,870 --> 00:19:02,871
[exhales]

339
00:19:03,496 --> 00:19:04,998
Until we die together,

340
00:19:05,874 --> 00:19:07,333
we'll say, "Ack!" together.

341
00:19:10,628 --> 00:19:12,297
-Ack!
-Ack!

342
00:19:12,380 --> 00:19:13,506
Ack!

343
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:14,632
[laughs]

344
00:19:15,341 --> 00:19:16,342
Time to turn them.

345
00:19:16,426 --> 00:19:18,636
No, they got
30 more seconds of cooking left.

346
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,889
-Oh, just do it.
-No way.

347
00:19:20,972 --> 00:19:22,432
It's time. Just try.

348
00:19:23,016 --> 00:19:24,225
[sighs]

349
00:19:25,143 --> 00:19:25,977
Huh?

350
00:19:26,853 --> 00:19:27,854
Well, what's this?

351
00:19:27,937 --> 00:19:30,565
I put more charcoal
when you weren't looking.

352
00:19:30,648 --> 00:19:31,566
[So-yeon laughs]

353
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:35,111
-[Gun-woo] When did you do that?
-[laughs]

354
00:19:38,698 --> 00:19:39,782
[music fades]

355
00:19:50,919 --> 00:19:52,003
-Thank you.
-[man] Of course.

356
00:19:52,086 --> 00:19:52,921
It's good.

357
00:19:54,505 --> 00:19:55,506
[car door closes]

358
00:20:00,386 --> 00:20:02,013
-[Min-beom] Grab two blue ones.
-[man] Yes.

359
00:20:02,513 --> 00:20:04,432
[poignant music playing]

360
00:20:04,515 --> 00:20:06,351
-[Woo-jin] Hmm.
-[Gun-woo] Mmm.

361
00:20:06,434 --> 00:20:08,186
-Let's have the neck meat now.
-[Gun-woo] Mm.

362
00:20:11,481 --> 00:20:14,776
-Oh my! Well, hello. Good to see you.
-Good evening, Ms. Yoon. Congratulations.

363
00:20:14,859 --> 00:20:15,860
Hello, Ms. Yoon.

364
00:20:15,944 --> 00:20:17,654
I'm sorry to bother you this evening.

365
00:20:17,737 --> 00:20:20,865
Oh, no, no, you're always welcome.
Come in! [chuckles nervously]

366
00:20:20,949 --> 00:20:22,283
I was on a business trip.

367
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:25,787
I went to Taiwan and I thought of you,
so I got you a little gift.

368
00:20:25,870 --> 00:20:28,665
-I hope you don't mind.
-Really? You shouldn't have. [gasps]

369
00:20:28,748 --> 00:20:30,041
Oh, it's so generous.

370
00:20:30,124 --> 00:20:31,376
Thank you so much.

371
00:20:31,459 --> 00:20:33,586
It's something small,
so accept it without obligation.

372
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:34,504
Oh, jeez.

373
00:20:34,587 --> 00:20:36,464
You always make delicious food
when I come here.

374
00:20:36,547 --> 00:20:40,093
Oh my, you're always welcome here.
Don't just stand there.

375
00:20:40,176 --> 00:20:41,427
-Thanks.
-[gasps]

376
00:20:43,304 --> 00:20:46,391
-Gun-woo, Woo-jin! Min-beom's here.
-Oh! Oh.

377
00:20:47,642 --> 00:20:48,643
Congratulations!

378
00:20:49,602 --> 00:20:51,104
-[Min-beom chuckles]
-Look what I have!

379
00:20:51,187 --> 00:20:53,481
-Oh, the belt! Wow, nice.
-It's big.

380
00:20:53,982 --> 00:20:56,317
I wanted to be there,
but my trip got extended.

381
00:20:56,401 --> 00:20:57,986
-I'm sorry.
-[Gun-woo] I understand.

382
00:20:58,069 --> 00:21:00,738
He clobbered his opponent in three rounds.
It finished quickly.

383
00:21:00,822 --> 00:21:02,240
That fast?

384
00:21:02,323 --> 00:21:03,157
[music stops]

385
00:21:03,241 --> 00:21:04,993
I've got good news myself.

386
00:21:05,076 --> 00:21:06,452
-Let's have a drink?
-Sounds good.

387
00:21:06,536 --> 00:21:07,578
Great. [chuckles]

388
00:21:08,788 --> 00:21:10,873
-[Min-beom] Well done, you two.
-[all] Cheers!

389
00:21:10,957 --> 00:21:12,792
[upbeat music playing]

390
00:21:14,252 --> 00:21:16,212
-[Min-beom] Drink all that at once?
-[exhales]

391
00:21:19,132 --> 00:21:20,216
[meat sizzles]

392
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:21,634
[Min-beom] Cheers!

393
00:21:25,471 --> 00:21:26,806
[chuckles]

394
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,768
[gasps happily]

395
00:21:33,855 --> 00:21:35,148
[Min-beom] Cheers!

396
00:21:40,153 --> 00:21:41,446
[blows] Ha.

397
00:21:41,529 --> 00:21:42,822
Mmm!

398
00:21:46,075 --> 00:21:47,493
[sighs]

399
00:21:47,577 --> 00:21:49,245
IIL SEOUL HOSPITAL
AERIAL RENDERING

400
00:21:49,329 --> 00:21:50,288
[music fades]

401
00:21:50,371 --> 00:21:51,331
Whoa.

402
00:21:51,414 --> 00:21:53,333
My new approved project.

403
00:21:53,416 --> 00:21:56,502
It's four floors underground,
ten floors above ground.

404
00:21:56,586 --> 00:21:58,421
When our nonprofit grows more,

405
00:21:58,504 --> 00:22:01,424
this is where I'll build
the pediatric hospital.

406
00:22:01,507 --> 00:22:02,884
Once we build that,

407
00:22:03,384 --> 00:22:05,011
we'll name the hospital

408
00:22:05,678 --> 00:22:08,389
Tae-ho Pediatric Clinic, after Mr. Choi.

409
00:22:10,183 --> 00:22:11,392
[poignant music playing]

410
00:22:11,476 --> 00:22:13,519
That's so freaking cool.

411
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,230
I know. [laughs]

412
00:22:16,314 --> 00:22:20,109
[all laugh]

413
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:23,613
Min-beom, Gun-woo,

414
00:22:24,405 --> 00:22:27,867
let's all raise our glasses
for those who aren't here.

415
00:22:28,368 --> 00:22:29,535
Friends in heaven?

416
00:22:29,619 --> 00:22:30,787
Let's say,

417
00:22:31,871 --> 00:22:32,914
"Thanks for everything."

418
00:22:34,165 --> 00:22:36,667
Yes. Mm.

419
00:22:37,251 --> 00:22:39,587
[all] Thanks for everything.

420
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:45,760
[exhales]

421
00:22:45,843 --> 00:22:48,012
[Min-beom] Yes, thank you.

422
00:22:49,097 --> 00:22:51,099
[ominous music playing]

423
00:22:59,857 --> 00:23:00,942
Where are we going?

424
00:23:02,443 --> 00:23:03,611
You will fight

425
00:23:03,694 --> 00:23:04,987
to pay your debt.

426
00:23:07,031 --> 00:23:07,865
Look at this.

427
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:10,451
Let's do it tomorrow.

428
00:23:11,452 --> 00:23:15,706
Tomorrow, there will be
a million-dollar interest.

429
00:23:16,207 --> 00:23:17,667
Ah, fuck!

430
00:23:18,835 --> 00:23:20,128
[laughs]

431
00:23:26,259 --> 00:23:28,136
[tense music playing]

432
00:23:35,935 --> 00:23:36,769
Take Adik.

433
00:23:42,150 --> 00:23:43,609
The fighter's here.

434
00:23:51,742 --> 00:23:52,869
[tense music builds]

435
00:24:09,719 --> 00:24:10,970
Hey.

436
00:24:14,474 --> 00:24:15,475
Put them in.

437
00:24:16,142 --> 00:24:16,976
For real?

438
00:24:18,144 --> 00:24:19,770
I can kill someone.

439
00:24:19,854 --> 00:24:21,397
It happens.

440
00:24:21,481 --> 00:24:22,440
[exhales]

441
00:24:23,191 --> 00:24:25,193
-[clattering]
-That's fucked up, man.

442
00:24:26,944 --> 00:24:28,070
-[sighs]
-[knife clicks]

443
00:24:30,114 --> 00:24:34,535
You losing over $3 million
in two hours in a poker game is fucked up.

444
00:24:35,036 --> 00:24:37,872
We know where your daughter lives.

445
00:24:38,664 --> 00:24:39,707
That's fucked up.

446
00:24:43,503 --> 00:24:44,462
Pick that up.

447
00:24:52,303 --> 00:24:55,264
Welcome to
the Iron Knuckle Fighting Championship.

448
00:25:00,102 --> 00:25:02,480
[breathes deeply]

449
00:25:17,495 --> 00:25:18,454
[chuckles]

450
00:25:18,955 --> 00:25:20,957
[suspenseful music playing]

451
00:25:25,002 --> 00:25:27,713
[man] Go in. You two, wait over there.

452
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:32,093
Okay, let's go, LOL.

453
00:25:32,593 --> 00:25:36,847
At last, the undisputed
WBC super middleweight champion,

454
00:25:36,931 --> 00:25:40,434
Adik Belov, just showed up at IKFC36.

455
00:25:40,518 --> 00:25:43,271
The showdown between the Hunter
and Bulldozer's about to begin!

456
00:25:43,354 --> 00:25:47,900
So better get the bets ready
'cause we're about to go down!

457
00:25:47,984 --> 00:25:49,986
[rock music playing]

458
00:25:51,904 --> 00:25:52,905
[music fades]

459
00:25:53,614 --> 00:25:54,991
[man] We've passed 300 million.

460
00:25:55,074 --> 00:25:58,911
We've now gone past 400 million.
Our commission will be 12 million.

461
00:25:59,453 --> 00:26:02,456
-How much is my amount?
-Well, more than if you were sleeping.

462
00:26:03,499 --> 00:26:06,210
Say exactly how much, motherfucker.

463
00:26:06,294 --> 00:26:08,296
[tense music playing]

464
00:26:08,796 --> 00:26:11,090
At least, maybe,
three times more than before.

465
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:19,515
-[music fades]
-[exhales sharply]

466
00:26:23,769 --> 00:26:25,771
[suspenseful music playing]

467
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:47,877
You motherfucker.

468
00:26:48,628 --> 00:26:51,255
I needed to ask for more money.

469
00:26:51,339 --> 00:26:54,383
'Cause you're too fucking easy!

470
00:26:58,596 --> 00:26:59,930
Let's start this.

471
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:01,599
[music stops]

472
00:27:01,682 --> 00:27:03,100
Let's fight!

473
00:27:05,519 --> 00:27:06,437
[grunts]

474
00:27:07,730 --> 00:27:10,816
[both huffing]

475
00:27:11,525 --> 00:27:13,319
[both grunting]

476
00:27:28,626 --> 00:27:30,086
[tense music playing]

477
00:27:38,969 --> 00:27:40,721
[heaving]

478
00:27:40,805 --> 00:27:42,098
[men grunt]

479
00:27:42,181 --> 00:27:43,015
-Ah!
-[grunting]

480
00:27:43,099 --> 00:27:44,809
[groaning]

481
00:27:45,434 --> 00:27:47,728
[both grunting]

482
00:27:52,149 --> 00:27:53,192
[yells in pain]

483
00:27:54,318 --> 00:27:55,986
[groans]

484
00:27:56,696 --> 00:27:57,822
[Belov groans]

485
00:27:59,699 --> 00:28:00,783
Destroying Adik now.

486
00:28:00,866 --> 00:28:04,161
Oh, shit. Look at Adik's face!

487
00:28:04,245 --> 00:28:06,163
-He's bitching! [laughs]
-[laughs]

488
00:28:06,247 --> 00:28:07,707
[fighters grunting]

489
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:08,708
[bones crack]

490
00:28:17,633 --> 00:28:18,718
[music fades]

491
00:28:18,801 --> 00:28:25,516
[panting heavily]

492
00:28:25,599 --> 00:28:26,809
Cameras off.

493
00:28:27,727 --> 00:28:28,769
[tense music playing]

494
00:28:28,853 --> 00:28:29,937
Cameras off now.

495
