744
00:43:49,064 --> 00:43:52,192
The four of them
are serving life sentences in prison.

745
00:43:52,275 --> 00:43:53,401
They all would be good.

746
00:43:53,485 --> 00:43:56,321
They've got a grudge against Kim Gun-woo
and his friend, Hong Woo-jin.

747
00:43:56,821 --> 00:43:58,615
If we can get them out of prison,

748
00:43:59,282 --> 00:44:02,035
we'll get relentless bloodhounds
that will never give up.

749
00:44:02,118 --> 00:44:03,495
Can we control them?

750
00:44:05,288 --> 00:44:06,539
I see why you're concerned.

751
00:44:06,623 --> 00:44:09,125
They won't have any choice
but to rely on us

752
00:44:09,209 --> 00:44:11,294
since they'll be wanted criminals.

753
00:44:11,378 --> 00:44:13,129
And if they help us get the job done,

754
00:44:14,130 --> 00:44:17,467
I'll throw a carrot and offer to help them
to escape to somewhere abroad.

755
00:44:17,550 --> 00:44:18,927
How much does that cost?

756
00:44:19,844 --> 00:44:22,305
100 million won. For each person.

757
00:44:25,850 --> 00:44:28,728
[sighs] Shitface.
That's fucking expensive.

758
00:44:28,812 --> 00:44:31,731
The profit's going to be
more than ten times the cost.

759
00:44:31,815 --> 00:44:33,650
You're full of shit.

760
00:44:37,529 --> 00:44:40,115
[sinister music builds]

761
00:44:52,335 --> 00:44:53,253
This one.

762
00:44:54,754 --> 00:44:56,339
The one I would've picked.

763
00:44:56,840 --> 00:45:01,553
There's a security company I always use
whenever I have VIPs visiting from abroad.

764
00:45:01,636 --> 00:45:03,805
The founders are
former presidential security agents,

765
00:45:03,888 --> 00:45:05,432
which means they're thorough.

766
00:45:05,515 --> 00:45:08,476
But recently, their sales director
and their CEO had a falling out.

767
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:12,772
By default, their hired hands
haven't been paid for a very long time.

768
00:45:14,023 --> 00:45:14,899
So what?

769
00:45:14,983 --> 00:45:17,902
There's a small risk
of things not going our way.

770
00:45:17,986 --> 00:45:21,114
Well, especially because gangsters
and ex-cons are rough.

771
00:45:21,614 --> 00:45:24,534
So in case Ms. Yoon gets hurt,
things could get really messy,

772
00:45:24,617 --> 00:45:26,369
which isn't what we want.

773
00:45:26,870 --> 00:45:29,497
So I recommend we use them,

774
00:45:29,581 --> 00:45:31,541
even if it costs a little more extra.

775
00:45:33,084 --> 00:45:37,714
[sighs] Shit, another way
to get extra funds? Just handle it.

776
00:45:40,300 --> 00:45:43,803
During jobs like these there are
all sorts of variables that might happen.

777
00:45:44,387 --> 00:45:48,933
That's why… you should
go with a bloodhound who has our back.

778
00:45:49,434 --> 00:45:51,895
That's a golden rule when I'm working.

779
00:46:01,863 --> 00:46:02,864
No mistakes.

780
00:46:02,947 --> 00:46:03,865
[music fades]

781
00:46:04,866 --> 00:46:06,409
Thanks for the payment.

782
00:46:12,749 --> 00:46:13,625
Hmm.

783
00:46:14,417 --> 00:46:15,877
Will you get these for me?

784
00:46:17,629 --> 00:46:20,465
GASOLINE, DDNP, SALTPETER
NICHROME, DETONATOR, CELL PHONE

785
00:46:20,548 --> 00:46:21,674
[chuckles]

786
00:46:23,718 --> 00:46:26,346
There's no reason
to go this far, Sergeant Yun.

787
00:46:26,429 --> 00:46:28,890
I need to be ready, Mr. Lee.

788
00:46:28,973 --> 00:46:30,058
[chuckles]

789
00:46:31,142 --> 00:46:32,060
Well,

790
00:46:33,186 --> 00:46:34,270
trust what I do.

791
00:46:34,354 --> 00:46:36,105
I still need to be ready and prepared.

792
00:46:37,649 --> 00:46:39,317
[laughs]

793
00:46:40,068 --> 00:46:41,694
[thudding]

794
00:46:46,491 --> 00:46:48,368
[In-beom grunts]

795
00:46:55,458 --> 00:46:56,543
[ominous music playing]

796
00:46:56,626 --> 00:46:57,460
TAO TE CHING

797
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:03,716
SWALLOW THIS AT 1 P.M. TWO DAYS FROM NOW
I'LL GET YOU OUT

798
00:47:16,312 --> 00:47:17,355
[music fades]

799
00:47:18,439 --> 00:47:20,942
[brakes squeal]

800
00:47:21,860 --> 00:47:23,736
[tense music playing]

801
00:47:40,587 --> 00:47:41,671
[car lock beeps]

802
00:47:44,007 --> 00:47:45,008
[exhales]

803
00:47:45,967 --> 00:47:47,343
[sighs with relief]

804
00:47:50,179 --> 00:47:51,264
[music fades]

805
00:47:52,307 --> 00:47:54,767
[man] With this last one,
you have eight in total.

806
00:47:54,851 --> 00:47:55,768
It should be good.

807
00:47:55,852 --> 00:47:57,520
-[Gun-woo] Thank you.
-[Woo-jin] Gun-woo!

808
00:47:57,604 --> 00:47:59,230
-You outside?
-[Gun-woo] Yeah.

809
00:48:01,316 --> 00:48:03,234
Adik's team is leaving today.

810
00:48:03,735 --> 00:48:06,446
Yet, Adik has disappeared.
He's gone missing.

811
00:48:06,529 --> 00:48:07,572
[sighs]

812
00:48:08,156 --> 00:48:10,575
UZBEK BOXER MISSING AFTER TITLE FIGHT.
POLICE INVESTIGATING.

813
00:48:10,658 --> 00:48:11,868
[breathes heavily]

814
00:48:11,951 --> 00:48:12,994
[tense music playing]

815
00:48:13,077 --> 00:48:14,245
I have a bad feeling, Woo-jin.

816
00:48:14,829 --> 00:48:17,749
I think those assholes are behind this.

817
00:48:22,462 --> 00:48:23,504
[music fades]

818
00:48:36,517 --> 00:48:37,685
[suspenseful music playing]

819
00:48:37,769 --> 00:48:39,020
[camera whirs]

820
00:49:04,462 --> 00:49:05,964
Sir, this is the job?

821
00:49:08,174 --> 00:49:09,175
It's just,

822
00:49:09,676 --> 00:49:11,511
why do we have to stoop so low?

823
00:49:12,804 --> 00:49:14,263
We're trained to protect.

824
00:49:14,347 --> 00:49:16,432
[man 1] How does it help to say this now?

825
00:49:17,558 --> 00:49:18,559
We agreed to do it.

826
00:49:20,561 --> 00:49:23,189
Don't you understand
we're about to go under?

827
00:49:23,690 --> 00:49:25,858
We need to pay the other guys too.

828
00:49:26,442 --> 00:49:28,486
Hey. They trusted us.

829
00:49:29,070 --> 00:49:31,406
They worked hard and what did they get?
Broken bodies.

830
00:49:31,489 --> 00:49:33,908
-Yes, I know that, of course, but--
-[man 2] Jin-nam.

831
00:49:34,993 --> 00:49:37,870
Stay in the car. We'll handle it.

832
00:49:38,579 --> 00:49:42,166
[sighs] Mr. Jang,
we can't finish the job with two.

833
00:49:43,459 --> 00:49:44,752
Let's give it a go.

834
00:49:44,836 --> 00:49:46,838
[tense music playing]

835
00:49:52,885 --> 00:49:56,305
[laughs]

836
00:49:56,389 --> 00:49:58,349
[beeping]

837
00:49:58,433 --> 00:49:59,434
[man 3] Bingo.

838
00:49:59,517 --> 00:50:00,351
FRONT DOOR

839
00:50:00,393 --> 00:50:01,227
[lock clicks]

840
00:50:07,942 --> 00:50:09,360
[outgoing call ringing]

841
00:50:10,945 --> 00:50:11,988
Yes?

842
00:50:12,572 --> 00:50:13,656
You can go in.

843
00:50:26,294 --> 00:50:27,295
[Jang] Let's do it.

844
00:50:29,547 --> 00:50:31,549
[dramatic music playing]

845
00:50:48,775 --> 00:50:50,902
[device whirs]

846
00:50:50,985 --> 00:50:52,987
[tense music playing]

847
00:51:12,507 --> 00:51:15,968
[breathes deeply]

848
00:51:40,618 --> 00:51:45,623
[So-yeon gasps, struggles]

849
00:51:51,129 --> 00:51:53,673
-[tense music builds]
-[muffled screaming]

850
00:51:58,594 --> 00:51:59,637
[music fades]

851
00:52:01,264 --> 00:52:02,557
Oh, Mom!

852
00:52:02,640 --> 00:52:04,225
[dramatic music playing]

853
00:52:04,308 --> 00:52:05,810
[both grunt]

854
00:52:08,521 --> 00:52:10,481
-[Woo-jin] Gun-woo!
-[Gun-woo] They're taking her.

855
00:52:12,066 --> 00:52:12,900
-My mom!
-Mom!

856
00:52:12,984 --> 00:52:14,986
-[Jang] Don't fight. I will.
-[man] It's my job.

857
00:52:18,823 --> 00:52:21,701
Shit! You fucker!

858
00:52:23,744 --> 00:52:24,662
[man groans]

859
00:52:26,622 --> 00:52:28,207
[man grunts, yells]

860
00:52:29,584 --> 00:52:32,545
[both grunting]

861
00:52:33,129 --> 00:52:34,213
[groans]

862
00:52:36,090 --> 00:52:38,593
[all grunting]

863
00:52:48,102 --> 00:52:49,979
-[Gun-woo] Woo-jin.
-What is it?

864
00:52:50,062 --> 00:52:51,856
-I've gotta go.
-What?

865
00:52:54,984 --> 00:52:56,110
Gun-woo, are you okay?

866
00:52:56,194 --> 00:52:57,445
[Gun-woo groans]

867
00:53:03,075 --> 00:53:04,285
[gasps]

868
00:53:05,244 --> 00:53:08,122
[panting]

869
00:53:08,873 --> 00:53:09,999
[grunts]

870
00:53:10,082 --> 00:53:13,961
[both straining]

871
00:53:19,258 --> 00:53:21,302
[both grunting]

872
00:53:33,272 --> 00:53:34,398
[groans]

873
00:53:34,482 --> 00:53:36,400
[both grunting]

874
00:53:45,201 --> 00:53:46,827
[groans]

875
00:53:55,002 --> 00:53:56,337
[Taser crackling]

876
00:53:58,714 --> 00:54:00,967
[all grunting]

877
00:54:02,218 --> 00:54:05,638
[groaning]

878
00:54:09,100 --> 00:54:10,017
[both straining]

879
00:54:10,101 --> 00:54:12,019
-[cries out] Ugh!
-[grunts forcefully]

880
00:54:14,438 --> 00:54:15,439
We've gotta go.

881
00:54:15,982 --> 00:54:17,024
[So-yeon groans]

882
00:54:17,650 --> 00:54:18,734
Agh!

883
00:54:19,568 --> 00:54:21,612
[straining]

884
00:54:21,696 --> 00:54:23,614
[Taser crackling]

885
00:54:23,698 --> 00:54:26,993
[all grunting]

886
00:54:27,076 --> 00:54:29,745
-[Taser crackling]
-[groaning]

887
00:54:31,747 --> 00:54:32,915
[grunts]

888
00:54:32,999 --> 00:54:34,959
[heaving]

889
00:54:35,042 --> 00:54:36,210
[both grunting]

890
00:54:36,794 --> 00:54:38,796
[both grunting]

891
00:54:57,940 --> 00:54:59,066
[Taser crackling]

892
00:55:11,037 --> 00:55:14,915
-Shit!
-[straining]

893
00:55:23,424 --> 00:55:25,134
[both straining]

894
00:55:36,729 --> 00:55:40,608
[Taser crackling]

895
00:55:42,026 --> 00:55:44,195
[Gun-woo groans]

896
00:55:45,363 --> 00:55:48,741
[Taser crackling]

897
00:55:48,824 --> 00:55:50,701
-[man groans]
-[bone cracks]

898
00:55:54,914 --> 00:55:56,582
-Oh, oh, oh!
-[man yells]

899
00:55:58,876 --> 00:55:59,794
[Gun-woo gasps]

900
00:55:59,877 --> 00:56:01,504
-[man groaning]
-[Jang] You okay?

901
00:56:01,587 --> 00:56:03,047
-[man] It hurts a lot!
-Gun-woo!

902
00:56:03,130 --> 00:56:05,174
[breathing heavily]

903
00:56:10,971 --> 00:56:12,890
[man groaning]

904
00:56:15,184 --> 00:56:17,269
[Jin] Come on, let's go. Let's leave now.

905
00:56:19,480 --> 00:56:20,564
[music fades]

906
00:56:20,648 --> 00:56:23,526
-[Woo-jin] You okay?
-[groans]

907
00:56:23,609 --> 00:56:26,612
-Here. Can you get up?
-No, my… My mom's there!

908
00:56:26,695 --> 00:56:29,073
-[Gun-woo panting]
-[tense music playing]

909
00:56:30,116 --> 00:56:31,826
[groaning]

910
00:56:31,909 --> 00:56:33,619
-[whimpering]
-Hold on, I've got you.

911
00:56:33,702 --> 00:56:35,579
[groans]

912
00:56:35,663 --> 00:56:38,249
[heaving]

913
00:56:38,332 --> 00:56:39,208
[engine revs]

914
00:56:39,917 --> 00:56:40,960
[Jin] Come on, let's go!

915
00:56:44,588 --> 00:56:45,423
Hey, stop!

916
00:56:46,257 --> 00:56:49,385
Get up! Let's go! Come on!

917
00:56:50,678 --> 00:56:52,680
[dramatic music playing]

918
00:56:53,931 --> 00:56:56,517
-[Jin] Drive faster! Floor it!
-[grunts]

919
00:57:14,535 --> 00:57:16,620
[panting]

920
00:57:16,704 --> 00:57:18,998
[grunts with frustration]

921
00:57:21,917 --> 00:57:24,795
-[groans]
-[exhales]

922
00:57:24,879 --> 00:57:30,926
[groaning continues]

923
00:57:36,474 --> 00:57:39,059
[brakes squeal]

924
00:57:48,402 --> 00:57:50,404
[tense music continues]

925
00:57:50,488 --> 00:57:53,199
[panting]

926
00:58:08,255 --> 00:58:09,298
[music fades]

927
00:58:09,381 --> 00:58:11,383
[dramatic music playing]

928
01:01:07,393 --> 01:01:08,394
[music fades]
